activities:
Brightstar Corp. and its US affiliates and subsidiaries (“Brightstar”) will use and otherwise process personal information received in the US about employees of its affiliates in Europe ("European Employee Data") for the following purposes: 
 
•	Workflow management, such as assigning, managing, and administering projects; 
•	Compensation, including stock plan administration and compensation analysis; 
•	Payroll processing; 
•	Performance management; 
•	Succession planning; 
•	Benefits and personnel administration, such as:
o	Health and medical benefits 
o	Leave entitlements 
o	Bonuses 
o	Pensions 
•	IT helpdesk and support services; 
•	Monitoring and enforcing compliance with company policies and procedures;
•	Job applications and advancement; 
•	Conducting engagement surveys; and
•	Meeting legal obligations.

Brightstar will use and otherwise process personal information received in the US about individual customers and the representatives of legal entity customers in Europe ("European Customer Representative Data") for the following purposes:  

•	perform obligations under its or its affiliates agreements with customers and carry out related business functions; and
•	assure compliance with legal obligations and regulations applicable to Brightstar and its affiliates.
